00:48:53,819 --> 00:48:55,150
[E-mail alert sounds]

759
00:48:55,254 --> 00:48:57,950
...at the messages
she got on Friday?

760
00:48:58,056 --> 00:49:01,617
[Chuckles] Yeah, that
whittles it down to, like, 200.

761
00:49:01,727 --> 00:49:04,287
Let me see.
It could be any one of these guys.

762
00:49:04,463 --> 00:49:07,091
Or none of them.
Half these guys are anonymous.

763
00:49:07,199 --> 00:49:08,188
[Beep]

764
00:49:08,300 --> 00:49:12,134
There's not much to go on.

765
00:49:12,237 --> 00:49:15,638
Maybe we can get them
to tell us what the profiles don't.

766
00:49:15,741 --> 00:49:19,438
Can you send them <i>all</i> a message?

767
00:49:19,544 --> 00:49:23,412
Um... write,

768
00:49:23,515 --> 00:49:25,642
"Durtygrrl knows what you are."

769
00:49:29,221 --> 00:49:31,485
Nice... flirtatious, yet threatening.

770
00:49:31,590 --> 00:49:33,251
Just send it.

771
00:49:37,529 --> 00:49:39,463
I don't know.
Do you think it will work?

772
00:49:39,564 --> 00:49:43,432
I mean, if I just did something shady,
I would be way on the D.L.

773
00:49:43,535 --> 00:49:45,833
Maybe.

774
00:49:45,937 --> 00:49:47,700
But you'd have to be curious.

775
00:49:47,806 --> 00:49:51,298
Wouldn't you want to know
if you got away with it?

776
00:49:54,579 --> 00:49:58,640
You know, we really
haven't had much time to talk...

777
00:49:58,750 --> 00:50:01,514
...recently.

778
00:50:05,424 --> 00:50:10,862
I guess I feel a little strange
leaving you by yourself.

779
00:50:10,962 --> 00:50:13,487
I'm a big girl.
I'll be fine.

780
00:50:13,598 --> 00:50:14,462
[Motion sensor snaps on]

781
00:50:14,566 --> 00:50:15,396
[Loud crash outside]

782
00:50:15,500 --> 00:50:17,229
God damn it!

783
00:50:17,336 --> 00:50:21,864
Honey, can you make sure the
raccoons aren't in the garbage again?

784
00:50:27,512 --> 00:50:32,245
[Insects buzzing]

785
00:50:32,351 --> 00:50:40,224
[Train whistles in distance]

786
00:50:42,794 --> 00:50:45,194
[Sarah screams]

787
00:50:45,297 --> 00:50:46,264
[Sarah gasping in a panic]

788
00:50:46,365 --> 00:50:49,163
OFFICER BERG:
Take it easy, now. Take it easy.

789
00:50:49,267 --> 00:50:51,462
You struggle too much,
you're liable to get hurt.

790
00:50:53,171 --> 00:50:55,139
<i>That's better.</i>

791
00:50:57,109 --> 00:51:01,011
Got a message from your friend.

792
00:51:01,113 --> 00:51:04,139
Seems like she's alive and well.

793
00:51:04,316 --> 00:51:09,413
Now, I don't know
what you think your game is,

794
00:51:09,521 --> 00:51:12,115
but you might
want to keep this in mind...

795
00:51:12,224 --> 00:51:14,385
[Breathes heavily]

796
00:51:14,493 --> 00:51:16,859
A man's family is his castle.

797
00:51:16,962 --> 00:51:18,429
[Train approaches scene, honks,
wheels clacking over tracks]

798
00:51:18,530 --> 00:51:22,557
Invade his castle,
well, that's an act of war.

799
00:51:22,667 --> 00:51:25,329
[Train whistle blowing long tones,
passing in immediate proximity]

800
00:51:25,437 --> 00:51:28,770
SARAH'S MOTHER:
Sarah? Everything okay?

801
00:51:28,874 --> 00:51:33,004
[Almost drowned out by train]
Sarah?

802
00:51:34,045 --> 00:51:36,013
I'll be watching you.

803
00:51:36,114 --> 00:51:36,637
SARAH:
[Gasps]

804
00:51:36,748 --> 00:51:37,476
[Motion sensor alert snaps off]

805
00:51:37,582 --> 00:51:39,641
SARAH'S MOTHER:
Sarah?

806
00:51:39,751 --> 00:51:41,810
Sarah?

807
00:51:44,055 --> 00:51:50,551
[Sobs]

808
00:51:55,333 --> 00:51:57,460
[Scream]

809
00:51:57,569 --> 00:51:58,695
Honey, time to get up.

810
00:51:58,804 --> 00:52:00,533
[Text message alert sounding]

811
00:52:00,639 --> 00:52:02,368
Come on! Get your clothes on.

812
00:52:02,474 --> 00:52:05,568
You have to drive me
to the airport, remember?

813
00:52:05,744 --> 00:52:06,870
I'm surprised
your phone didn't wake you.

814
00:52:06,978 --> 00:52:08,502
It's been beeping all night.

815
00:52:08,613 --> 00:52:09,875
[Alert sounds again]

816
00:52:11,450 --> 00:52:17,184
[Alerts continue]

817
00:52:36,341 --> 00:52:37,501
MR. PALOMINO:
<i>When you guys finish,</i>

818
00:52:37,609 --> 00:52:39,042
<i>I need someone up here on the floor.</i>

819
00:52:39,144 --> 00:52:40,941
SARAH:
Okay.

820
00:52:43,081 --> 00:52:44,742
Well, what do you
want to do with these?

821
00:52:57,929 --> 00:53:00,227
I thought you were
morally opposed to cigarettes.

822
00:53:00,332 --> 00:53:02,994
Daddy says they are a dirty habit.

823
00:53:06,638 --> 00:53:08,469
What's it like
just living with your dad?

824
00:53:09,875 --> 00:53:13,333
It's all right.

825
00:53:13,445 --> 00:53:15,504
It used to be more fun
before Mom died.

826
00:53:18,650 --> 00:53:19,446
What happened?

827
00:53:20,852 --> 00:53:24,310
Complications in childbirth.

828
00:53:26,157 --> 00:53:27,181
With my baby brother.

829
00:53:27,292 --> 00:53:29,658
After that, Dad got really strict,

830
00:53:29,761 --> 00:53:33,697
and now I have lots of rules on...

831
00:53:33,798 --> 00:53:37,632
...the Internet and makeup and stuff.

832
00:53:37,736 --> 00:53:38,862
Yeah.

833
00:53:42,307 --> 00:53:43,865
Oh, heck!

834
00:53:43,975 --> 00:53:45,408
There's my dad. He's coming.

835
00:53:45,510 --> 00:53:45,999
SARAH:
[Stamping out cigarettes]

836
00:53:46,111 --> 00:53:46,634
Don't panic. Don't panic.
It's fine.

837
00:53:46,745 --> 00:53:48,975
- Um, spray some of this on.
- No! I can't wear perfume!

838
00:53:49,080 --> 00:53:50,980
Darla, do you want your dad
thinking that you're wearing perfume

839
00:53:51,082 --> 00:53:51,810
or smoking?

840
00:53:54,019 --> 00:53:56,579
Uh, okay, hit me...

841
00:53:57,122 --> 00:53:58,316
Vince!

842
00:53:58,423 --> 00:54:01,256
Darla, ring up your dad, will you?

843
00:54:01,359 --> 00:54:02,348
Take it easy.

844
00:54:03,495 --> 00:54:06,589
- Hi, sweetheart.
- Hi.

845
00:54:06,765 --> 00:54:08,824
Hi, Sarah.

846
00:54:08,934 --> 00:54:10,925
I notice you've been down
to the library quite a bit lately.

847
00:54:11,036 --> 00:54:12,833
Are you in summer school?

848
00:54:12,938 --> 00:54:16,203
No, um... It's like
a personal research project.

849
00:54:17,709 --> 00:54:19,404
- Oh.
- These are $5.30.

850
00:54:19,511 --> 00:54:21,843
- Okay. All right. There you go.
- Thank you.

851
00:54:22,514 --> 00:54:25,711
- Have you heard from your friend?
- My friend?

852
00:54:25,817 --> 00:54:30,413
Yes, the, uh, the young lady
who was working here. Jillian?

853
00:54:31,556 --> 00:54:33,183
No, uh, not yet.

854
00:54:33,892 --> 00:54:36,554
I'm sure she'll turn up.
Thanks.

855
00:54:38,530 --> 00:54:41,795
All right. Bye, honey.

856
00:54:41,900 --> 00:54:43,731
You're not wearing perfume, are you?

857
00:54:43,835 --> 00:54:45,803
Oh, no, um, that's me.

858
00:54:45,904 --> 00:54:50,773
I think I, I think I was standing
next to her when I sprayed it on.

859
00:54:51,910 --> 00:54:53,639
Okay.

860
00:54:53,745 --> 00:54:56,043
All right.
I'll see you later tonight.

861
00:54:57,182 --> 00:54:57,876
Hey, Daddy?

862
00:54:59,384 --> 00:55:02,182
I invited Sarah over to our house
for my birthday.

863
00:55:05,557 --> 00:55:07,889
Good! Good!

864
00:55:07,993 --> 00:55:09,984
Well, we'll have
a good time, won't we?

865
00:55:10,095 --> 00:55:13,189
It'll be a nice party.
Okay.

866
00:55:16,501 --> 00:55:19,732
Thanks for covering for me!
You will come, won't you?

867
00:55:19,838 --> 00:55:21,328
This Sunday.

868
00:55:21,439 --> 00:55:23,839
I'm sorry about telling him
about the Jillian thing.

869
00:55:23,942 --> 00:55:25,671
- I didn't mean anything by it.
- Oh, it's okay.

870
00:55:25,777 --> 00:55:29,873
Um, yeah, of course I'll come.
It'll be really fun.

871
00:55:37,389 --> 00:55:39,084
[Tapping keyboard]

872
00:55:40,025 --> 00:55:41,117
Any bites?

873
00:55:41,793 --> 00:55:42,350
JASPER:
[Whistles]

874
00:55:42,460 --> 00:55:44,985
Are you gonna read all those?

875
00:55:45,096 --> 00:55:46,961
[Alert sounds]

876
00:55:47,065 --> 00:55:48,396
Well, better get started!

877
00:55:48,500 --> 00:55:53,301
[Music plays]

878
00:56:16,661 --> 00:56:18,128
Thought you could use a boost.

879
00:56:18,229 --> 00:56:21,289
- Just hook up an I.V.
- What, boring?

880
00:56:21,399 --> 00:56:21,990
[Sighs]

881
00:56:22,100 --> 00:56:22,930
Let me give you a sample.

882
00:56:23,702 --> 00:56:25,499
"I know that you're
the girl of my dreams.

883
00:56:25,603 --> 00:56:27,468
Hit me back. Let's hook up."

884
00:56:27,572 --> 00:56:28,937
He misspelled "girl".

885
00:56:29,040 --> 00:56:31,770
It just goes on and on.
It's like that or worse.

886
00:56:31,876 --> 00:56:35,710
Like every cheesy little perv-boy
on the Internet was her friend.

887
00:56:36,848 --> 00:56:42,218
She gets these messages from Peru
and Bangladesh and France.

888
00:56:42,320 --> 00:56:43,378
This girl never left Goshen.

889
00:56:48,426 --> 00:56:50,018
Slide over.

890
00:56:50,128 --> 00:56:51,356
It's dead in here.
I'll take a shift.

891
00:56:51,463 --> 00:56:54,330
[Music keeps playing]

892
00:57:13,718 --> 00:57:19,281
[Train whistle in distance]
[E-mail alert sounds]

893
00:57:21,392 --> 00:57:24,327
Sarah, why are we doing this?

894
00:57:24,429 --> 00:57:25,919
She's my best friend.

895
00:57:26,030 --> 00:57:28,624
Yeah, I know. I know. I get that.

896
00:57:28,733 --> 00:57:30,724
But this...

897
00:57:30,835 --> 00:57:33,599
This is like above
and beyond best friends.

898
00:57:33,705 --> 00:57:37,402
I guess it's because
I know if I got into trouble

899
00:57:37,509 --> 00:57:40,842
I would always
have my mom and dad.

900
00:57:40,945 --> 00:57:41,877
And I think that most people

901
00:57:41,980 --> 00:57:44,949
have somebody who cares
about what happens to them.

902
00:57:45,049 --> 00:57:47,279
And the only person Jill has is me.

903
00:57:52,190 --> 00:57:54,351
I don't know what I'm doing.

904
00:57:54,459 --> 00:57:55,517
[Sighs]

905
00:57:55,627 --> 00:57:57,185
I have to open tomorrow.

906
00:57:57,295 --> 00:57:59,388
Yeah. I should lock up.

907
00:57:59,497 --> 00:58:00,964
Oh!

908
00:58:01,065 --> 00:58:02,498
[Grumbles]

909
00:58:02,600 --> 00:58:07,230
[E-mail alert sounds]

910
00:58:07,405 --> 00:58:11,034
Hey! What did you say
Jillian was calling this guy?

911
00:58:11,142 --> 00:58:12,234
A "Mr. X."

912
00:58:12,343 --> 00:58:13,674
You'd better check this out.

913
00:58:14,746 --> 00:58:15,735
Here. Look.

914
00:58:15,847 --> 00:58:17,542
- JASPER: Look at the name.
- SARAH: Mr. eXperience?

915
00:58:17,649 --> 00:58:19,014
Mr. X! How did I miss that?

916
00:58:19,117 --> 00:58:20,175
He's still online.

917
00:58:39,003 --> 00:58:40,664
- Do you think this is our guy?
- I'm trying to find that out.

918
00:58:43,508 --> 00:58:46,375
Hey, he's logged off.

919
00:58:46,477 --> 00:58:47,944
[Sighs]

920
00:58:48,046 --> 00:58:51,743
What the hell does that mean?

921
00:58:53,051 --> 00:58:55,781
[Insects buzzing]

922
00:58:55,887 --> 00:58:57,787
[Car alarm deactivates]

923
00:59:06,431 --> 00:59:09,093
Jillian?

924
00:59:13,171 --> 00:59:15,139
Jillian?

925
00:59:42,267 --> 00:59:43,256
Jillian?

926
00:59:43,368 --> 00:59:45,393
[Door slams]

927
00:59:54,479 --> 00:59:58,813
[Traffic passes]

928
00:59:59,250 --> 01:00:02,014
[Echoing whisper]
<i>Sarah.</i>

929
01:00:02,120 --> 01:00:04,054
<i>Up here.</i>

930
01:00:07,158 --> 01:00:10,685
[Glass bottles fall]

931
01:00:27,512 --> 01:00:28,410
Jillian?

932
01:00:37,522 --> 01:00:41,891
[Scream]
[Objects crash]

933
01:00:41,993 --> 01:00:44,359
[Gasping]

934
01:00:44,462 --> 01:00:47,022
[Gasping]

935
01:00:47,131 --> 01:00:48,291
Patty?

936
01:00:56,174 --> 01:00:58,438
[Door squeaks on hinges]

937
01:00:58,543 --> 01:01:00,408
Oh!
[Gasping]

938
01:01:01,446 --> 01:01:03,641
I know what you are, too.

939
01:01:14,826 --> 01:01:16,293
[Exhales]

940
01:01:18,930 --> 01:01:21,057
Now...

941
01:01:21,165 --> 01:01:23,497
...how long you say
your friend's been missing?

942
01:01:23,601 --> 01:01:28,436
- A couple of weeks.
- Couple of weeks?

943
01:01:29,340 --> 01:01:34,607
My Janet was gone three years
before I realized.

944
01:01:35,580 --> 01:01:39,641
Me and her old man,

945
01:01:39,751 --> 01:01:42,720
we didn't get on so well...
I'm sure you've heard the stories.

946
01:01:45,156 --> 01:01:48,353
Day doesn't go by
that I don't hate myself

947
01:01:48,459 --> 01:01:52,520
for leaving her
with that son-of-a-bitch.

948
01:01:52,630 --> 01:01:54,029
Her "Daddy."

949
01:01:56,100 --> 01:01:57,761
By the time I faced up to him,

950
01:01:57,869 --> 01:02:01,862
she was gone
and he didn't know where.

951
01:02:01,973 --> 01:02:04,134
Is that when you started
putting up flyers?

952
01:02:04,242 --> 01:02:07,075
Being a lowlife has its advantages.

953
01:02:07,245 --> 01:02:10,976
People underestimate you,
but I'm focused.

954
01:02:11,082 --> 01:02:17,214
I traveled, looked under a lot
of rocks, lived under a few, too.

955
01:02:17,789 --> 01:02:18,983
[Glass bottle falls over]

956
01:02:20,892 --> 01:02:24,225
I've heard some stories.

957
01:02:24,328 --> 01:02:25,886
Like what?

958
01:02:25,997 --> 01:02:31,731
Children... disappearing.

959
01:02:31,836 --> 01:02:38,901
The kind of kids <i>nobody's</i> looking for.
The kind of kids <i>they</i> call "trash."

960
01:02:39,010 --> 01:02:44,277
"Runaway."
Like... Brenda Stills,

961
01:02:44,382 --> 01:02:46,179
Cindy Marker,

962
01:02:46,284 --> 01:02:47,581
Debbie Hope.

963
01:02:49,287 --> 01:02:51,346
Like your Jillian.

964
01:02:51,456 --> 01:02:54,357
Like my Janet.

965
01:02:54,459 --> 01:02:58,418
[Motorcycle revs in distance]

966
01:02:58,529 --> 01:02:59,996
All lost.

967
01:03:01,365 --> 01:03:02,889
PATTY:
They're all lost.

968
01:03:08,039 --> 01:03:11,236
Sometimes when I...

969
01:03:11,342 --> 01:03:12,969
...feel her slipping away from me,

970
01:03:13,077 --> 01:03:17,207
I call her just to listen
to her voice on the message...

971
01:03:17,315 --> 01:03:21,684
...so I don't forget what she...

972
01:03:21,786 --> 01:03:24,983
...sound like.

973
01:03:28,726 --> 01:03:30,250
Where did you get that?

974
01:03:30,361 --> 01:03:32,761
- It's Jillian's!
- Jillian's?

975
01:03:35,466 --> 01:03:37,195
It's The Serpent himself!

976
01:03:37,301 --> 01:03:38,529
The serpent?

977
01:03:39,270 --> 01:03:43,206
- The devil.
- Patty, I don't know what that means.

978
01:03:44,041 --> 01:03:46,601
You can't see it in the flyers
because the copies are for crap,

979
01:03:46,711 --> 01:03:48,645
but on the original...

980
01:03:48,746 --> 01:03:50,839
...it's clear as day.

981
01:03:50,948 --> 01:03:53,382
Holy shit!

982
01:03:54,485 --> 01:03:57,249
[Dialing number]

983
01:03:58,256 --> 01:04:01,316
[Phone ringing]

984
01:04:01,425 --> 01:04:03,791
Come on, Jasper. Pick up.
Come on.

985
01:04:03,895 --> 01:04:07,592
[Phone vibrates]

986
01:04:07,765 --> 01:04:09,562
Come on, Jasper.

987
01:04:09,667 --> 01:04:14,127
[Vibrations continue]

988
01:04:14,238 --> 01:04:15,466
[Phone ringing]

989
01:04:15,573 --> 01:04:16,062
[Gasps]

990
01:04:16,174 --> 01:04:16,640
Shit.

991
01:04:22,713 --> 01:04:24,578
[Dog barks]

992
01:04:25,616 --> 01:04:28,642
Oh, my God!
Oh, my God!

993
01:04:28,753 --> 01:04:30,345
Jasper!

994
01:04:33,224 --> 01:04:34,589
Look.

995
01:04:34,692 --> 01:04:37,058
[Jasper groans]

996
01:04:37,161 --> 01:04:37,957
SARAH:
Fuck!

997
01:05:06,557 --> 01:05:09,720
[Sighs]

998
01:05:37,989 --> 01:05:39,684
He just went in back.

999
01:05:39,790 --> 01:05:43,351
Well, right on schedule.
Every day at 2:00 Billy hits the glue.

1000
01:05:43,461 --> 01:05:45,929
Yeah, give him a couple of minutes.
You'll see.

1001
01:05:46,030 --> 01:05:48,396
And you know this how?

1002
01:05:48,499 --> 01:05:50,433
I collect model trains, all right?

1003
01:05:50,534 --> 01:05:54,265
Have you ever tried to buy miniatures
from a stoner? It freaks them out.

1004
01:05:54,372 --> 01:05:56,306
You sure it was Billy last night?

1005
01:05:56,407 --> 01:05:59,103
The guy has tortured me
my entire life.

1006
01:05:59,210 --> 01:06:02,145
I think I can recognize his voice.

1007
01:06:02,246 --> 01:06:06,148
Okay. Let's get him.

1008
01:06:36,914 --> 01:06:38,745
BILLY:
<i>Um...</i>

1009
01:06:38,849 --> 01:06:41,340
<i>... hold on a second.</i>

1010
01:06:44,922 --> 01:06:46,412
[Paintball gun firing]

1011
01:06:46,524 --> 01:06:48,685
Agh!

1012
01:06:48,793 --> 01:06:50,317
What the fuck?

1013
01:06:50,428 --> 01:06:52,896
Ah! Oh!

1014
01:06:52,997 --> 01:06:54,828
- Hey, Billy!
- Oh, man!

1015
01:06:54,932 --> 01:06:56,524
We just want to ask you
a few questions.

1016
01:06:56,634 --> 01:06:58,659
I'm on fucking duty any day...

1017
01:06:58,769 --> 01:07:01,465
[Paintball gun fires]
[Gags]

1018
01:07:01,572 --> 01:07:04,598
First question...
when you jumped Jasper last night,

1019
01:07:04,709 --> 01:07:07,337
you said, "I know who you are, too."

1020
01:07:07,511 --> 01:07:09,274
How did you know
we sent that message?

1021
01:07:09,380 --> 01:07:11,177
[Hoarsely] You tell me.
You're the honor student.

1022
01:07:11,282 --> 01:07:12,840
[Paintball gun fires]
Ugh!

1023
01:07:12,950 --> 01:07:14,247
Ow!

1024
01:07:14,352 --> 01:07:17,321
Well, I can guess the first part,
that you knew Jillian was Durtygrrl.

1025
01:07:17,421 --> 01:07:19,651
It's the connection to Jasper
that I'm missing.

1026
01:07:22,226 --> 01:07:23,523
Okay, okay. Okay. Okay.

1027
01:07:23,627 --> 01:07:25,322
I knew...

1028
01:07:25,429 --> 01:07:28,159
[Stuttering]... how you think
you're such a genius, Ass-per.

1029
01:07:28,466 --> 01:07:30,331
Nobody's heard from J in weeks.

1030
01:07:31,135 --> 01:07:33,729
And all of a sudden
she's sending me messages

1031
01:07:33,838 --> 01:07:36,102
with your ugly face
all over her profile.

1032
01:07:36,207 --> 01:07:39,699
[Laughs]
You'd never make Jay's Top 8.

1033
01:07:39,810 --> 01:07:42,074
You'd never even
make her Top 800.

1034
01:07:43,047 --> 01:07:45,880
I bet that really
pissed you off, right?

1035
01:07:45,983 --> 01:07:48,315
That Jillian had a profile like that
to meet men.

1036
01:07:48,419 --> 01:07:51,320
Yeah, and we all know you
do stupid things when you're angry.

1037
01:07:51,422 --> 01:07:54,084
Yeah, it pissed me off.
That was the point, wasn't it?

1038
01:07:54,191 --> 01:07:56,386
To piss me off.

1039
01:07:56,494 --> 01:07:58,553
Jay was always doing stupid shit.

1040
01:07:58,662 --> 01:08:00,926
She was always
playing games with me,

1041
01:08:01,031 --> 01:08:03,192
telling me how many guys
wanted to fuck her.

1042
01:08:04,635 --> 01:08:07,297
I never thought
she was serious, though.

1043
01:08:07,471 --> 01:08:10,304
[Gasping]

1044
01:08:10,408 --> 01:08:11,375
What do you know, Billy?

1045
01:08:13,077 --> 01:08:14,601
Now you've got a choice.

1046
01:08:14,712 --> 01:08:17,078
Face or nuts?
You can't cover them both.

1047
01:08:17,181 --> 01:08:20,014
Okay, okay, okay.
Okay. Fuck you.

1048
01:08:21,819 --> 01:08:23,980
Okay, I followed her...

1049
01:08:24,088 --> 01:08:26,022
...okay, after the party.

1050
01:08:27,758 --> 01:08:31,717
I thought it was part of the,

1051
01:08:31,829 --> 01:08:33,592
part of the game.

1052
01:08:33,697 --> 01:08:36,632
You know, she'd get me all mad,
and then I'd...

1053
01:08:36,734 --> 01:08:38,827
[Jillian screams]
...you know.

1054
01:08:38,936 --> 01:08:40,699
I followed her downtown.

1055
01:08:41,138 --> 01:08:43,163
And then I saw her get into a...

1056
01:08:43,274 --> 01:08:44,639
